race.comment: COUPLES RETREAT (1) was ridden quietly then unleashed and proved a shade too good when resuming over this course and distance last start. Talented mare who is proven in town so these provincial benchmark races are perfect for her. Up in the weights but can win again. ALL THE WAY MAE (7) has raced twice this prep, both times here at 1000m, and despite being a warm favourite on each occasion has travelled handy then weakened. Lightly raced filly who clearly has more to offer so give her one more chance. CANI CANCAN (2) is racing well but the wins are hard to come by. Got going late to grab fourth in open company at Moruya last time. Beautifully drawn and always runs well at five furlongs. GHIELMI (4) has led for home but been overwhelmed at both runs this prep. Rock-hard fit now and should give them something to catch. RAINBOW GLOW (8) has switched from Bjorn Baker to Ciaron Maher since failing in the Listed Woodlands at Scone in May. Market watch advised.
